I'm afraid that is inaccurate,(in fact, it is wrong). A clear cloudless day-time sky is blue because molecules in the air scatter blue light from the sun more than they scatter red light. When we look towards the sun at sunset, we see red and orange colors because the blue light has been scattered out and away from the line of sight, due to the angle the light hits the atmosphere. At this angle it scatters red light because of the dust, soot, pollen etc in the air.
